<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-05-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-05-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="704" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d704">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/18171</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Bowman</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Frontera</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-05-16">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 16, 1916</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Mayor of Frontera has received instructions from Governor to organize
                            the citizens for defense, treating the question of a war as a certainty
                            but not yet declared. Americans have not been ill-treated though usual
                            threats from irresponsible people have been made.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bowman</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>